<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Tutamun:
[I] :div: Demo Bugs & Suggestions:
- There is no sound for the "Hell Spikes" Spell. Only when they hit an enemy the make a sound.

- Sound scrambles a bit when I ALT-TAB away from  :div: or return to  :div:. Sound is fine again if I stay away from  :div: for a while or when I stay in the game for a while.

- How can you unasign a hot key from a potion?

- When pressing CTRL F11 while over a potion I noticed the following: If you release CTRL right after pressing F11 then the Hotkey "F11" is assigned. If you hold the CTRL key for a while then "CTRL F11" is assigned. Btw. you can then drink a potion and make a Screenshot at the same time  ;)

- When making your own health or mana potions and you pick them up they don't stack with the ones you bought. The health/mana potions buttons show the number of self made potions until you click on it to drink a potion. Then the number of bought potions is shown. I think that self made shadow, strength and restoration potions do stack with the bought or found potions.

- One thing I thought about when fighting rats... What happens when you are something like level 10, 20 or higher. The rats with level 1 wouldn't have a chance in fighting you. Why do they then try? Okay, maybe if there are 10 or 20... but with only 2 or 3? Hmm... I think that they should rather run away.

It could become a bit anoying if you later in the game have to kill a large group of weak oponents because they always bother you (stand around you and try to hit you). You need to klick once on every enemy. In Dungeon Siege your Hero fights on his own (which I don't really like)... but that would solve this problem.

Have you tried to implement that [b]really[/b] weak opnonents rather run away or at least don't attack your character on their own? This could depend on the inteligence of the oponent. I don't like theese suicide rushes seen in most other games. But when they run away it could be anoying for the "Diablo" Style players because the have to run after the oponents to be able to kill everyone and everything.  >:)

Because of this I thought it would be better to let them stay a bit away and not attack on their own. Only when the Character comes too close or attacks them then they defend themselves. (They might even run off to get reinforcement.)

The skeletons seen in the Demo arn't really smart so I wouldn't expect this behaviour from them... and you can see what happens to the smart ones  :D But I'd really like to know what happend to the planned AI in  :div: Will it be noticable? Your sight radius is rather small so you can't see what your oponents are currently doing. Because of that I'm a bit concearned that you won't notice the smart AI that might be there  >:)[/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
